<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>play hard to get • play hardball</xh5><p> <i>play hard to get—</i>pretend to be unapproachable or uninterested, with a view to strengthening one’s position: To be blunt, you sort of strike me as <u>playing hard to get</u>.</p><p><i>play hardball—</i>use uncompromising tactics: The insurance company <u>played hardball</u> with desperate homeowners, relying on questionable experts, and falsified reports.</p> </entry>
